          <section class="poem">
            <h2 class="title">Dueling Haikus on Facebook</h2> 
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> The way to write haiku:</p>
            <p>What?<br>
            Really?<br>
           WOW!</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Ro Hith</span> and <span class="fb">6 others</span> like this.</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Jeff Wright</span> Really? Wow!
         What?!</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> No, no. You miss the point.</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Jeff Wright</span> Birdlight in the boom pall / I feel slight / <br>
            worker dragging a garbage can</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> Too cumbersome. Think minimal.</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Jeff Wright</span> Drinking coffee at
            my screen / endless drone outside /<br> 
            I cool my jets</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> Want
            to learn? <br>
            Think of nothing.<br> Fetch!<br> KJG 19 Jan 2013</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Rick Anderson</span> that’s
            not Haiku, that’s Hijinks</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Jeff Wright</span> Way to go!<br> Show me the ropes.<br> Fall
            back.</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> Show and tell.<br> Whatchu got?<br> Aw, you dropped it!<br>
            KJG 19 Jan 2013</p>
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> Smile. </p>
            <p><span class="fb">Jeff Wright</span> Heat coming up.<br>
              Listen.<br> Sun getting high. </p>
            <p><span class="fb">Klaus J. Gerken</span> Snowing here. Crunch. </p>
          </section>
